Instruction: With power removed and all fast-connect terminals unplugged, use a multimeter in continuity/ohms mode to map the two conductors that run from Control Module 2 output to Control Module 3 input, then 3→4, 4→5, 5→6, 6→7, 7→8, and 8→Load Module. For each adjacent pair of modules, (1) identify which terminals at the upstream module are continuous to which terminals at the downstream module; (2) verify that one continuous conductor forms an unbroken 12 V line all the way from the previously identified Control Output Cable (+) 1 to the Load Module input (+), and that the other continuous conductor forms an unbroken 0 V line from Control Output Cable (−) 1 to the Load Module input (−); (3) note any segment where the two conductors are swapped, open, or cross-connected.
