With power removed, open Control Module 1’s access panel enough to probe its internal PCB around the missing green indicator LED and its series resistor. Using a multimeter in ohms/continuity mode, (1) identify the two pads or terminals where the LED/resistor branch should connect to the 12 V and 0 V rails; (2) measure resistance between those pads and the corresponding external (+) and (−) terminals of Control Module 1 to confirm they are correctly tied (low resistance) and not cross‑connected; (3) measure resistance directly between the two pads that formerly went to the LED/resistor to see whether they are now open, shorted, or inadvertently bridged. Record whether any unintended short or open exists that could be inserting extra series resistance or breaking continuity for the downstream chain.
